AS TO COUNT 1 -   
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 11 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 175 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 6 YEARS.  
Court costs and surcharges restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Complete 500 hours of community service (100 hours per year); 
2) No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause; 
3) Successfully complete a cognitive intervention program;
4) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
5) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
6) Absolute sobriety with random urine screens; 
7) Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
8) No contact with co-defendant Dominic Collins 14CF440;
9) Seek/maintain fulltime employment;
10) Obtain GED/HSED; 
11) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
12) Pay all supervision fees;
13) Restitution set at ZERO;
14) Pay applicable costs, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge and assessments; any balance remaining unpaid is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant. 
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting.
